@NODE create-adapted-screen-modes "Create adapted Screen Modes"
@SMARTWRAP
@{CODE}@{FG Shine}@{b}  +-------------------------------+
 /  Create adapted Screen Modes  /
+-------------------------------+
@{ub}@{FG Text}@{PAR}@{BODY}@{LINDENT 1 }
@{LINE}Some arcade games have non-standard resolution, and none of your Screen Mode would really fit. Intuition will choose a larger resolution that will make your game appear little. You can either configure streight-to-border scaling, but that will slow down. The best solution is to create an adapted screen mode with the tool installed by your Retargetable graphics library.@{LINE}Mame will then be able to choose those new modes after reboot.@{LINE}@{LINE}Games that usually have unadapted screens and modes OK for a 16x9 screen:@{LINE}@{LINE}Capcom CPS1 machines (street fighterII,strider,3wonders,shoulsnghost,...) is almost 16/9. it will need @{b}mode "384x224 HiColor".@{ub}@{LINE}@{LINE}midTUnit (Mortal Kombat,NBA Jam) will need @{b} mode "456x256 HiColor"@{ub}.@{LINE}@{LINE}Gauntlet and lots of atari games  will need  @{b}mode "426x240 HiColor"@{ub}.@{LINE}@{LINE}(For a 5/4 screen or other screen ratio, consider a missing resolution should have same height as emulated screen, then compute the width with a rule of 3, and round it to the next 16 multiple. Hey, easy math ! ask your AI if you can't do that.)@{LINE}@{LINE}About the retargetable library version:@{LINE}We don't recommend that you install the last supported version, as numberous new bugs appeared on recent ones, with no corrections of the bugs we reported. Anyway, it doesn't matter much as you may be using either cafeineOS or amikit, your version is probably already the best possible, and workarounds has been found for most problems.@{LINE}@{LINE}@{" Display: Image of P96 screen mode tool " SYSTEM "multiview guideimg/p96prefs.png"}@{LINE}@{LINE}@{LINDENT 3}@{LINE}- 1. Create a new resolution: In the “Resolutions” section, create a new entry by dragging the “New Item” icon to the “Resolutions” area.@{LINE}
- 2. Configure the resolution: Fill in the resolution details, such as width, height,.@{LINE}
- 3. Add color modes: For each resolution, you must add color modes also by dragging New button on the right list, then select color mode in cycle menu. Note 256 colors correspond to 8bit Mame screens, HiColor to 15 or 16Bit, TrueColor to 32 bits.You should create the 3 color Modes.@{LINE}
- 4. Test the resolution: Once you’ve created and configured the new resolution, press the “Test” button to see the result on your HDMI output.@{LINE}
- 5. You May have to unselect "doubleScan" if pixels are too narrow.@{LINE}
@{LINE}
@{LINDENT 1}@{LINE}Save your settings, reboot, and you should have excellent fast fullscreen display for most games.@{LINE}@{LINE}
@{LINE}
@ENDNODE
@NODE using-a-rotated-screen-for-vertical-shooters "Using a rotated screen for Vertical Shooters"
@SMARTWRAP
@{CODE}@{FG Shine}@{b}  +------------------------------------------------+
 /  Using a rotated screen for Vertical Shooters  /
+------------------------------------------------+
@{ub}@{FG Text}@{PAR}@{BODY}@{LINDENT 1 }
A lot of arcade games had vertical screens, which were actually rotated CRT screens, with the Beam going left to right instead of Up to Down. This was the case for Vertical Shooters. Mame MiniMix allows you to choose any rotation in the Display Panel. With a monitor that allows rotation (like iiYama Xub), you can play Vertical shooters with a vertical screen.@{LINE}@{" Display: Using an Amiga1200 with a vertical shooter and vertical screen " SYSTEM "multiview guideimg/vertical.gif"}@{LINE}@{LINE}
@{LINE}
@ENDNODE
@NODE finetuning-audio-with-ahiprefs "Finetuning audio with AHIPrefs"
@SMARTWRAP
@{CODE}@{FG Shine}@{b}  +----------------------------------+
 /  Finetuning audio with AHIPrefs  /
+----------------------------------+
@{ub}@{FG Text}@{PAR}@{BODY}@{LINDENT 1 }
MAME106Minimix uses the default AHI Mode for audio output.@{LINE}@{LINE}With tool Sys:prefs/AHI you can choose this default mixing mode, and configure it.@{LINE}@{LINE}An audio mixer can use the Amiga native Paula sound chip, or another chip using a sound card if you own that.@{LINE}If your AHI installation is well configured, you can achieve an excellent sound even with Paula, and you will also be able to launch several apps using AHI at the same times and listen all of them, which is impossible without AHI.@{LINE}@{LINE}This is a very well known thing amongst Amiga users:@{LINE}@{LINE}AHI provide a 14Bits mixer that theorically push ups the classic 8Bit rendering to 14Bit precision using hardware trick.@{LINE}MAME106Minimix sends 16bit precision audio Data to AHI, so the 14Bit mixer may benefit from that. You should also at least ask for 22050 Khz of frequency, which gives actually good quality. Paula can't reach the modern CD-like 44Khz, its limit is 27Khz (or 33Khz if...).@{LINE}You may also choose the number of Channels available. This is said that choosing more channels lower the volume down on some drivers and AHI implementations (untested).@{LINE}@{LINE}@{" Display: Image of AHIPrefs screen mode tool " SYSTEM "multiview guideimg/ahiprefs.gif"}@{LINE}@{LINE}
@ENDNODE
@NODE aga-and-ocs-amiga-native-display "AGA and OCS Amiga native display"
@SMARTWRAP
@{CODE}@{FG Shine}@{b}  +------------------------------------+
 /  AGA and OCS Amiga native display  /
+------------------------------------+
@{ub}@{FG Text}@{PAR}@{BODY}@{LINDENT 1 }
@{LINE}From version 1.3 if you don't have any P96 or CGX video driver installed, MAME Minimix will be able to choose a 256,32 or 16 color screen mode. Now color remap is more precise, and original screen size will be adapted.@{LINE}You can choose explicitly a PAL or NTSC video mode, now the color depth is selectable (8b,7b,6b,5b,4b,...).@{LINE}With PiStorm, video memory writing is all the more slow that the sound thread is also using the bus to write audio.@{LINE}@{LINE}Finetune your AHI to use short audio buffers. You should install patch "BlazeWCP" (WCP for WriteChunkyPixels() ) from aminet.net, that will accelerate native rendering by 15 or 20% and accelerate all your OS. Do not install obsolete patch NewWPA8.@{LINE}You can also use Frameskip option.@{LINE}@{LINE}@{LINE}
@{LINE}
@ENDNODE
@NODE running-68060-version-on-amiga-os4-ppc "Running 68060 version on Amiga OS4 PPC"
@SMARTWRAP
@{CODE}@{FG Shine}@{b}  +------------------------------------------+
 /  Running 68060 version on Amiga OS4 PPC  /
+------------------------------------------+
@{ub}@{FG Text}@{PAR}@{BODY}@{LINDENT 1 }
@{LINE}The executable is compiled for 68060 with FPU with double float support, and the OS4 68k emulation stack called Petunia does not support it in JIT mode. Disabling JIT with tool SYS/Prefs/Compatibility has been reported to make it work ( This should be a bug report at Hyperion, remember anything can be corrected if correctly reported. ).@{LINE}Also Minimix r1.4 has a nasty bitmap copy optimization that doesn't work on OS4, this code should be now automatically disabled since r1.5 if layers.library version is (>=50).  else disable optimisation in Misc Panel. A better idea would be to port Minimix on OS4, it just wouldn't benefit the 68k specific optimisations. Note there are many other MAME ports on Amiga OS4 available at os4depot.@{LINE}@{LINE}@{LINE}
@{LINE}
@ENDNODE
@NODE installing-free-demoscene-demo-roms "Installing free Demoscene Demo ROMs"
@SMARTWRAP
@{CODE}@{FG Shine}@{b}  +---------------------------------------+
 /  Installing free Demoscene Demo ROMs  /
+---------------------------------------+
@{ub}@{FG Text}@{PAR}@{BODY}@{LINDENT 1 }
@{LINE}Demoscene productions are third party homebrew ROMS you can install without any legal issues, they are usually not games but nice visual effects with music, and art. *MAME106Minimix* is the only version of MAME with (currently) 3 demos internally registered as known roms in its internal database:@{LINE}@{LINE}@{LINDENT 5}@{LINE}- arkcrsn5.zip is provided in directory roms with the official MAME106Minimix package, it could be done because it weight a few kilobytes. This "Cruisin 5 roms by Abyss (2024)" demo uses the 8Bit hardware emulation of original Taito "Arkanoid" machine from 1985. This demo was originaly made because the coder actually own such hardware, and created this by replacing the 5 roms.@{LINE}
@{LINE}- Demo "Vaporous" by TTE was made in 2025, won a competition at Revision party, and is an extra neogeo romset. It is quite big, so unlike "cruisin'5" you have to download it at: https://files.scene.org/view/parties/2025/revision25/oldskool-demo/tte25-vaporous.zip . To install the demo:  unzip tte25-vaporous, rename file mame/mslug2.zip as vaporous.zip and copy it to roms: it uses same rom mapping as mslug2, but we do have a slot name as "vaporous" with correct rom hash and information in list, so you can have both vaporous and mslug2 in the same roms directory, that way.@{LINE}
@{LINE}- We also officialy support Oxygene's neogeo3D demo from 2012 (sound not working at the moment, but still impressive). Download it at https://www.pouet.net/prod.php?which=59253 , rename puzzledp.zip as neogeo3d.zip (so you can enjoy both and have correct name display) and copy it to roms/ .@{LINE}
@{LINE}
@{LINDENT 1}@{LINE}And that's it, you have demos on your arcade emulator.@{LINE}@{LINE}
@{LINE}@{LINE}
@ENDNODE
